OL,3,CHospice warns #130,000 national
OL,4,Cinsurance cost will mean 'reduction in
OL,5,Cservices'
OL,7,FWhile the NHS and the rest of the
OL,8,Fpublic sector are exempt from the tax
OL,9,Fhike, private care homes and hospices
OL,10,Flike St Luke's will soon be paying
OL,11,F#130,000 more in national insurance a
OL,12,Fyear.
OL,14,FThe hospices Chief Executive Neil
OL,15,FWright said: "It puts pressure on the
OL,16,Fservice. Normally when prices go up
OL,17,Fwith inflation, you can pass those on
OL,18,Fto your customers, but we don't charge
OL,19,Fout patients. Our special care is
OL,20,Fdelivered for free, so any increases
OL,21,Fwe have to deal with ourselves."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/9
